From 9ab7c1d377fe5e04b0bb23336da16f5883b9dae4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilia Alshanetsky <ilia@ilia.ws>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 13:25:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Lowercase \uXXXX hex digits via yyjson vendor patch (resolves
 todos/002)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

In-place modification of vendor/yyjson/yyjson.c's esc_hex_char_table:
'A'..'F' -> 'a'..'f' across the 512-byte hex pair table starting at
line 8442 in 0.12.0. yyjson 0.12 has no flag for hex digit case;
the table is hardcoded by the upstream make_tables.c generator.

vendor/yyjson/PATCHES.md documents the patch (P-001) with the
reproducible sed range so it can be re-applied on yyjson upgrades.
The .upstream/yyjson.yml freshness gate already pings new releases,
so we'll know when to re-apply.

Effect: byte-for-byte parity with ext/json on \uXXXX escapes.
"héllo" -> '"h\\u00e9llo"' instead of yyjson's default
'"h\\u00E9llo"'. RFC 8259 §7 allows either case, so the spec
isn't violated either way; the divergence mattered for callers
comparing encoded output byte-for-byte (cache-key fingerprints,
content-hash dedup, snapshot tests).

Compat harness gain:
  Before:  29 / 32 upstream-json tests passing, 66 in skiplist.
  After:   37 / 40 upstream-json tests passing, 58 in skiplist.

Net: +8 passing tests. The other ~17 upstream tests previously
skipped under todos/002 had compounded reasons (UTF-8 message text,
PARTIAL_OUTPUT_ON_ERROR, U+2028 line-separator escaping, depth
semantics) that the hex patch alone wouldn't fix. Re-categorized
under their primary cause in the skiplist.

todos/002 renamed to indicate resolved status; analysis preserved
for context. Combined own + upstream suite: 56 / 59 pass, 0 fail
(3 environment-skip).
---
